Baetis melanonyx (Pictet, 1843): 30 larvae (7 larvae mounted with Liquide de Faure), Czech Republic, Usti nad Labem district, Elbe river-basin, Divoka Orlice River, Lisnice village, 432 m a.s.l., 2.vii.1972, leg. T. Soldan (for details see
